
[1]coparcener

   COPARCENER, n. [con and parcener, L., to divide.] A coheir; one who has
   an equal portion of the inheritance of his or her ancestor with others.

   All the coparceners together make but one heir, and have but one estate
   among them.

   Coparceners take by descent; joint-tenants, by purchase.
